significantly enhance the infectivity and minimize the difference in susceptibility among different RaACE2 variants, an N501D substitution in SARS-CoV-2 S protein displays marked disparity in transduction efficiencies among RaACE2 variants with a significant reduction in infectivity on several RaACE2 variants. Finally, a T372A substitution in RaTG13 S protein not only significantly increases infectivity on all RaACE2 variants, but also markedly enhances entry on several bat ACE2s including\n              R\n              .\n              sinicus\n              YN,\n              R\n              .\n              pearsonii\n              , and\n              R\n              .\n              ferrumeiqunum\n              . However, the T372A mutant is about 4-fold more sensitive to neutralizing sera from mice immunized with BANAL-20-52 S, suggesting that the better immune evasion ability of T372 over A372 might contribute to the natural selective advantage of T372 over A372 among bat CoVs. Together, our study aids a better understanding of coronavirus entry, vaccine design, and evolution.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Li, Pei", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hu, Jiaxin", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Liu, Yan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ou, Xiuyuan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mu, Zhixia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lu, Xing", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zan, Fuwen", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cao, Mengmeng", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tan, Lin", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dong, Siwen", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zhou, Yao", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lu, Jian", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jin, Qi", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wang, Jianwei", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wu, Zhiqiang", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zhang, Yingtao", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Qian, Zhaohui", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Menachery, Vineet D.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity",